Hospital won't fix me.

1258
01:41:13,580 --> 01:41:15,039
But maybe you could, though.

1259
01:41:15,040 --> 01:41:16,416
You could help.

1260
01:41:17,292 --> 01:41:18,293
How?

1261
01:41:19,169 --> 01:41:20,337
Well, at school,

1262
01:41:21,505 --> 01:41:25,008
bring an object from each
of your classmates home to me.

1263
01:41:26,093 --> 01:41:27,260
That might work.

1264
01:41:28,637 --> 01:41:30,222
How will that make you better?

1265
01:41:33,934 --> 01:41:36,061
It might be just what I need.

1266
01:41:39,231 --> 01:41:41,733
And if you got better,
you'd go back home?

1267
01:41:45,695 --> 01:41:47,197
If I got better...

1268
01:41:49,533 --> 01:41:50,951
I'd go back home.

1269
01:42:51,928 --> 01:42:52,929
Alex.

1270
01:42:54,890 --> 01:42:56,432
What are you doing in here?

1271
01:42:56,433 --> 01:42:59,059
Um, I didn't
feel like playing,

1272
01:42:59,060 --> 01:43:01,146
and I forgot something.

1273
01:43:02,564 --> 01:43:04,524
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hey, hey, hey.

1274
01:43:07,986 --> 01:43:08,987
Are you okay?

1275
01:43:09,613 --> 01:43:11,072
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

1276
01:43:12,032 --> 01:43:14,701
You've been
awful quiet lately.

1277
01:43:15,368 --> 01:43:16,536
Quieter than usual.

1278
01:43:17,204 --> 01:43:18,246
How are you doing?

1279
01:43:18,789 --> 01:43:21,249
I'm okay.
I just forgot something.

1280
01:43:22,167 --> 01:43:23,168
It's okay.

1281
01:43:25,295 --> 01:43:26,754
Alex, you know,

1282
01:43:26,755 --> 01:43:29,466
if... you ever want to talk
to someone,

1283
01:43:29,966 --> 01:43:31,384
you can always talk to me.

1284
01:43:32,969 --> 01:43:34,178
Do you know that?

1285
01:43:34,179 --> 01:43:35,346
Yeah.

1286
01:43:35,347 --> 01:43:37,682
You can talk to me
about anything you want.

1287
01:43:41,186 --> 01:43:42,562
I wanna go back now.

1288
01:43:44,481 --> 01:43:46,441
Okay. Go play.

1289
01:44:43,748 --> 01:44:45,000
What are you doing?

1290
01:46:33,066 --> 01:46:34,151
No...

1291
01:46:43,952 --> 01:46:46,203
<i>Stephen here suffered
a stroke a little while back,</i>

1292
01:46:46,204 --> 01:46:48,080
<i>so he's unable to speak.</i>

1293
01:46:48,081 --> 01:46:50,750
<i>And I'm taking care of
the family for the time being.</i>

1294
01:46:51,251 --> 01:46:52,960
I'm glad you both are here.

1295
01:46:52,961 --> 01:46:55,171
Alex, how are you doing, pal?

1296
01:46:55,172 --> 01:46:56,505
I'm okay.

1297
01:46:56,506 --> 01:46:58,132
Now, we're gonna ask you
some questions

1298
01:46:58,133 --> 01:47:00,051
about what happened
at school, okay?

1299
01:47:02,387 --> 01:47:04,222
Tomorrow,
people will come here.

1300
01:47:05,849 --> 01:47:07,768
And they will search
this house...

1301
01:47:12,439 --> 01:47:14,232
and we have to be ready.

1302
01:47:33,585 --> 01:47:35,127
Detective, come in!

1303
01:47:35,128 --> 01:47:36,212
Good morning, Ms. Lilly.

1304
01:47:36,213 --> 01:47:37,463
- How are you today?
- Fine.

1305
01:47:37,464 --> 01:47:39,298
- Good to see you again.
- Nice to see you too.

1306
01:47:39,299 --> 01:47:41,008
- Remember Detective Colbert?
- Oh, yes.

1307
01:47:41,009 --> 01:47:43,469
We just wanted to come by the
house for a few minutes today

1308
01:47:43,470 --> 01:47:44,762
and look around, uh,

1309
01:47:44,763 --> 01:47:47,723
see the environment
that Alex has been living in.

1310
01:47:47,724 --> 01:47:51,268
And just get an idea of what
the family dynamic is like.

1311
01:47:51,269 --> 01:47:53,521
- Okay!
- Oh. Thank you.

1312
01:47:53,522 --> 01:47:54,605
And... Oh.

1313
01:47:54,606 --> 01:47:56,525
Hey, Alex.
How are you doing today?

1314
01:47:57,567 --> 01:47:58,818
He's a little quiet today, right?

1315
01:47:58,819 --> 01:48:00,612
- Mm-hmm. Yes, he is.
- Okay.

1316
01:49:05,051 --> 01:49:06,136
Hello?

1317
01:49:14,936 --> 01:49:17,105
Pack your things, Alex,
we're leaving tomorrow.

1318
01:49:20,275 --> 01:49:21,902
Don't step over the salt.

1319
01:49:54,893 --> 01:49:57,312
The cops are here.
What do you think that means?

1320
01:49:59,689 --> 01:50:00,732
I don't know.

1321
01:50:02,067 --> 01:50:03,484
Do we knock? Do we come back?

1322
01:50:03,485 --> 01:50:05,028
Maybe we knock.

1323
01:50:05,529 --> 01:50:08,240
And say what? What...
What are we gonna explain?

1324
01:50:11,243 --> 01:50:12,118
Yeah, I don't know.

1325
01:50:12,119 --> 01:50:13,245
- Let's just...
- Here we go.

1326
01:50:14,871 --> 01:50:16,081
Hey, what is this?

1327
01:50:29,094 --> 01:50:30,137
Is that the cop?

1328
01:50:31,471 --> 01:50:32,972
That's Paul.

1329
01:50:32,973 --> 01:50:35,016
- You know him?
- Yeah.

1330
01:51:15,599 --> 01:51:16,600
Hello?

1331
01:51:31,782 --> 01:51:32,783
Paul?

1332
01:51:46,129 --> 01:51:48,631
Paul,
what are you doing back there?

1333
01:51:48,632 --> 01:51:49,548
Wait.

1334
01:52:35,637 --> 01:52:37,179
Fuck! Fuck!

1335
01:52:38,557 --> 01:52:39,891
Stay fucking back!

1336
01:52:49,901 --> 01:52:51,068
Paul.

1337
01:52:51,069 --> 01:52:52,320
Paul, stop.

1338
01:52:53,238 --> 01:52:54,239
Stop!

1339
01:53:18,555 --> 01:53:19,598
God.

1340
01:53:22,017 --> 01:53:23,268
Goddamn it.

1341
01:53:41,495 --> 01:53:43,246
You goddamn freaky little...

1342
01:54:25,205 --> 01:54:27,916
Paul. Please.

1343
01:54:33,547 --> 01:54:34,548
Please.

1344
01:55:24,097 --> 01:55:25,098
Matthew?

1345
01:55:26,683 --> 01:55:27,684
Matthew!

1346
01:55:29,060 --> 01:55:30,061
No.

1347
01:55:30,687 --> 01:55:31,688
Matthew.

1348
01:55:33,148 --> 01:55:34,107
No.

1349
01:56:05,764 --> 01:56:06,765
Matthew?

1350
01:56:07,265 --> 01:56:08,308
Come on.

1351
01:56:10,310 --> 01:56:11,353
Matthew?

1352
01:56:13,230 --> 01:56:14,231
Who...

1353
01:56:53,061 --> 01:56:55,146
That's good.
Just like that.

1354
01:57:07,284 --> 01:57:09,536
That's the way.

1355
01:57:12,956 --> 01:57:14,124
Oh, no.

1356
01:58:00,003 --> 01:58:01,129
Oh, God!

1357
01:59:01,565 --> 01:59:04,650
Get off of me! Get off of me!

1358
01:59:53,325 --> 01:59:54,326
Matthew?

1359
02:00:16,932 --> 02:00:17,890
Honey, look outside.

1360
02:00:17,891 --> 02:00:19,475
Look what they did
to the yard.

1361
02:00:19,476 --> 02:00:21,894
Jeremy,
there's glass everywhere.

1362
02:00:21,895 --> 02:00:23,729
Find her shoe! My god!

1363
02:00:23,730 --> 02:00:25,231
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

1364
02:00:25,232 --> 02:00:27,024
Now there's a man
in the kitchen!

1365
02:00:33,156 --> 02:00:34,241
Alex?

1366
02:01:17,993 --> 02:01:18,994
Matthew?

1367
02:01:30,881 --> 02:01:32,299
Oh, I found you.

1368
02:01:39,055 --> 02:01:40,389
<i>Alex's parents are still</i>

1369
02:01:40,390 --> 02:01:42,309
<i>being fed soup somewhere.</i>

1370
02:01:42,893 --> 02:01:44,186
<i>But not by him.</i>

1371
02:01:46,188 --> 02:01:49,065
<i>He moved to another town and
lives with a different aunt.</i>

1372
02:01:50,400 --> 02:01:52,944
<i>I heard that one
is a nice lady.</i>

1373
02:01:55,322 --> 02:01:57,240
<i>All of the kids from his class</i>

1374
02:01:57,866 --> 02:01:59,910
<i>got reunited
with their parents.</i>

1375
02:02:01,912 --> 02:02:05,081
<i>Some of them even started
talking again this year.</i>

